mission.en-US: The mission of Skills Online Private Limited is to lead a Post-COVID-19 Digital Restoration of Sri Lanka by using Skill Development to Fuel Digital Innovation with 4th Industrial Revolution Technologies. We want Sri Lanka to become a global hub for AI, data science, cloud native computing, edge computing, blockchain, augmented reality, and internet of things. Our main objective is that our graduates of the program are employable in the international software outsourcing and freelancing marketplaces. Therefore, the programs will prepare students for international certification programs when available.

content.value: Skills Online Classes should be held online so that everyone can participate from home.
The fee should be low so that everyone can afford.

All students will be required to choose at least one of the following technical tracks with a duration of 12 to 18 months: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Cloud Native and Mobile Web Computing, Blockchain, and Internet of Things (IoT)

It will compulsory for all the students to take the innovation track covering the following
subjects: Design Thinking, Lean Startup, Agile, DevOps (Linux, Docker, Serverless Containers, Kubernetes, Terraform, CI/CD, and Prometheus)
We will follow the syllabus of
international certifications

where available and will
prepare the students for these international exams. We will also encourage the
students to appear in these international exams if they can afford it. The
objective of all the program is to get the students ready for the global market.
Every track will focus on teaching extensively one or more of the following open source programming languages: Python, JavaScript/TypeScript, Rust, Web Assembly
All tracks will teach students to develop end-to-end applications in addition to the specialized track course.
We will focus on open source technologies as much as possible.
Every student will continuously be evaluated by appearing in online exams. Final comprehensive exam will be proctored.
All faculty selection is based on the skills being taught and ability to communicate.

shortDescription.en-US: A one year program AI program in Data Science, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning.

content.value: A one year program AI smart application development program in Data Science, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning. In this program we will learn to develop smart AI based end-to-end applications. The program consists of two tracks i.e. sequence of courses which run a parallel:
AI Technical Track
Innovation Track

In the technical track, in order to learn end-to-end application development, we cover five main areas: Python programming, deep learning with Tensorflow 2, AI model deployment with Kubernetes and Kubeflow, micro services development using Flask, and Progressive Web App Development (React) using React and JavaScript.

Innovation has always been an efficient and effective tool to resolve the
challenges we face in software development. However, in this new era of
digital restoration during and after the COVID-19 crisis, digital innovation will play a
major part in restoring global prosperity. In the long term, the crisis will spur
and stimulate advancements in digital technology. Digital innovation and AI technologies (covered in the technical track) will have to play a major part we want to have our lives back.

In the innovation track we will cover both the art and science of innovation. Our innovation model combines Design Thinking, Lean Startup and DevOps. We cover will the following technologies: Linux, Git, Docker Containers, Terraform, Serverless Containers, CI/CD pipelines, and Prometheus. The innovation track will start in the second quarter of the program in parallel to the AI technical track.
Core Programming Language: Python
Secondary Programming Language: JavaScript/TypeScript
Main Libraries and Frameworks: TensorFlow, NumPy, Pandas, Flask, and React
Secondary Libraries and Frameworks: Kubernetes, and Kubeflow
